        <briefdescription>
<para>Called when the trait is being detached from the host view. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This method is invoked before the trait is removed from the view&apos;s storage. Use this to release the strong reference and perform cleanup, such as disconnecting from signals to prevent dangling pointers or leaks.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>This will not be called if the attached view is being destroyed. OnViewDestroying is called instead.</para>
</simplesect>
